	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f18317><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=search.shtml?id=3311&mid=18317>Hermit Stats</a> <a id=fs8 href=search.shtml?id=3311&mid=18317#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Zanen</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 14th 11:09 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To answer a previous question, the hermit hits for a max of 42.&nbsp;&nbsp;His melee skills seem to improve substantially when he carries his FS, which is always a short sword, long sword or 2H.  For 19 and 20 necros, he is possibly the easiest yellow/even con u will face in the game.  Either walk to the wall, and he hits you, or say the key phrase "kill you."  Sometimes he doesn't come out of the wall, so walk to the door and stand in front of it.  Cast heat blood, darkness, and when he comes at you fear.  Also, I know that casters have to med, but put your pets on guard so they will point to the nearest enemy.  This should help you spot the gnoll earlier and prevent something nasty, because they have between 800-950 hp and hit for a max of 64.  They also resist all spells heavily until lvl 24.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
